HEADWORD: Chanterelle
<hw>Chan`te*relle"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A name for several species of mushroom, of which
one (<spn>Cantharellus cibrius</spn>) is edible, the others reputed
poisonous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chantey</ent>⟦br⟧
